mparative tools to unify biogeography. Rooted in phylogenetic systematics, this comparative biogeographic approach offers a comprehensive empirical framework for discovering and deciphering the patterns and processes of the distribution of life on Earth. The authors cover biogeography from its fundamental ideas to the most effective ways to implement them. Real-life examples illustrate concepts and problems, including the first comparative biogeographical analysis of the Indo-West Pacific, an introduction to biogeographical concepts rooted in the earth sciences, and the integration of phylogeny, evolution and earth history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBiogeography. 7aSCIENCE / Earth Sciences / Geography.2bisacsh  abiodiversity.  abiogeographical patterns.  abiogeography.  abiology.  aclassification.  acollege students.  acomparative biogeographical analysis.  acomprehensive guide.  aearth history.  aearth sciences.  aempirical framework.  aevolution.  aexamples.  ageological history.  aindo west pacific.  alife distribution.  alife on earth.  anonfiction.  aphylogenetic systematics.  aphylogeny.  aresearch method.  ascience problems.  ascientific concepts.  ascientific discoveries.  aspecies distribution.  aspecies identification.  asystematics.  atextbooks.  aunified approach.1 aEbach, Malte, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025945440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094439840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520944398423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520944398/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013